highlight.contents: only one entry in the bucket address table points to bucket j. Therefore, the system needs to increase the size of the bucket address table so that it can include pointers to the two buckets that result from splitting bucket j.Itdoesso by considering an additional bit of the hash value.

highlight.name: 56d03803-ac09-d0f3-2e0d-c1c2215ad4ef
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: It increments the value of i by 1, thus doubling the size of the bucket address table. It replaces each entry with two entries, both ofwhich contain the same pointer as the original entry. Now two entries in the bucket address table point to bucket j.

highlight.name: f0a05f45-e00e-eb2e-1856-bf09d9a93b61
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: The system allocates a new bucket (bucket z) and sets the second entry to point to the new bucket. It sets ij and iz to i.

highlight.name: 1a0b051e-0893-e42a-f28a-038d980c9388
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: it rehashes each record in bucket j and, depending on the ﬁrst i bits (remember the system has added 1 to i), either keeps it in bucket j or allocates it to the newly created bucket.

highlight.name: 0b2b094c-4358-9fc0-754c-ff76a675b056
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: The systemnow reattempts the insertion ofthe new record. Usually, the attempt will succeed. However, if all the records in bucket j, as well as the new record, have the same hash-value preﬁx, it will be necessary to split a bucket again, since all the records in bucket j and the new record are assigned to the same bucket.

highlight.name: 960b7578-6ecf-f2ce-71ff-4c5bfed09b5f
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: more than one entry in the bucket address table points to bucket j. Thus, the system can split bucket j without increasing the size ofthe bucket address table.

highlight.name: e6c69ef9-c76b-9a94-afdf-bd50048362df
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: . The system allocates a new bucket (bucket z), and sets ij and iz to the value that results from adding 1 to the original ij value.

highlight.name: 8c4c39aa-b2d1-bd23-600d-5328d08a92ee
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: as in the previous case, the system rehashes each record in bucket j,and allocates it either to bucket j or to the newly created bucket z.

highlight.name: 04db9f46-bde3-cceb-a505-e4fca7c23c0b
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: The system then reattempts the insert. In the unlikely case that it again fails, it applies one of the two cases, i = ij or i > ij, as appropriate.

highlight.name: 1975cd5b-853e-e3c0-7aac-5e707560a286
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: Note that, in both cases, the system needs to recompute the hash function on only the records in bucket j.
